data.title: Jane Child
data.meta_description: Jane Child. Soundtrack: Freejack - Geisel der Zukunft. Jane Child was born on 15 February 1967 in Scarborough, Ontario, Canada. She is an actress and composer, known for Freejack - Geisel der Zukunft (1992), Jane Child: Don't Wanna Fall in Love (1990) and Die Mafiosi-Braut (1988). She has been married to Cat Grey since 2004.
data.text:
Her version of Tina Turner's "We Don't Need Another Hero" appears on "What's Love? A Tribute To Tina Turner".

Jane Child, with a long braided hair, spiky top hair in the early 1990s. She sings and plays various instruments including synthesizers, keyboards, guitar, violin, and more. The Top 5 1990 Billboard hit "Don't Wanna Fall In Love" which it had made it to #2 in 1990.

Released her 2nd album, "Here Not There", in August 1993, which contains the song, "Mona Lisa Smiles", featured in the movie Freejack - Geisel der Zukunft (1992).
